# Offer Letter — AI Intern

Date: 2025-12-01

To: [Candidate Name]  
Position: AI Intern  
Company: Omninuera  
Location (work arrangement): Remote (candidate will be located in Bengaluru)  
Start Date: [Start Date]  
Duration: 3 months (fixed-term internship)

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you the position of AI Intern at Omninuera for a fixed-term internship of three (3) months beginning on the Start Date noted above (to be completed by HR). This offer letter summarizes the principal terms and conditions of the internship. This is a draft and will be sent to Legal for review; it may be amended following Legal feedback.

1. Role and Responsibilities  
- Title: AI Intern.  
- You will work on projects and tasks as assigned by your manager relevant to AI research, model development, data processing, and other duties consistent with an intern role. Specific project assignments, deliverables, and supervisor expectations will be agreed with your manager at the start of the internship.

2. Term and Status  
- This position is a fixed-term internship for a period of three (3) months. The internship is not a regular full-time employment. The relationship is fixed-term (not open-ended) and will end on the term end date unless extended in writing by Omninuera and you. The fixed-term status means your position will automatically terminate at the end of the 3-month term unless an extension is agreed in writing.  
- This offer does not create any obligation for continued employment beyond the fixed-term, nor does it confer the benefits or status of a regular full-time employee.

3. Working Arrangement and Hours  
- Work arrangement: Completely remote. You will be located in Bengaluru.  
- Suggested weekly commitment: approximately 20 hours per week, or as otherwise agreed with your manager. The internship allows flexibility in scheduling; however, you and your manager should agree on expected weekly hours and key meeting times.

4. Stipend and Payment Terms  
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.  
- Payment schedule: The stipend will be paid monthly, on or by the last working day of each month.  
- Taxes and deductions: Omninuera will withhold taxes or make statutory deductions as required by applicable law. You are responsible for your personal tax filings and any taxes due on stipend payments as applicable. Omninuera may provide documentation of payments for your records.

5. Early Termination and Notice  
- End of term: The internship will end on the fixed-term end date (Start Date + 3 months) unless extended in writing.  
- Early termination for convenience: Either party may terminate the internship before the scheduled end date for convenience by providing at least seven (7) days' written notice to the other party.  
- Termination for cause: Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including but not limited to breach of confidentiality, misconduct, dishonesty, gross negligence, or material failure to perform duties. In such circumstances, termination may be effective immediately and without prior notice.  
- Intern-initiated termination: You may terminate the internship early by providing at least seven (7) days' written notice to your manager.

6. Confidentiality and Return of Materials  
- During your internship and thereafter, you must keep confidential and not disclose any Omninuera confidential information, trade secrets, proprietary data, or client information obtained during your internship, except as authorized in writing by Omninuera.  
- Upon termination or at Omninuera's request, you must promptly return or securely delete all Omninuera property and confidential materials, including hardware, documents, data, and any copies thereof.

7. Intellectual Property and Work Product Ownership  
- You agree that all inventions, discoveries, developments, improvements, works of authorship, code, data, designs, models, and other work product (collectively, "Work Product") created, conceived, developed, or reduced to practice by you, individually or jointly with others, during the internship and in the scope of your assigned duties, shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera.  
- To the extent permitted by applicable law, you hereby assign and agree to assign to Omninuera all right, title, and interest in and to such Work Product and any related intellectual property rights. You agree to promptly execute any documents reasonably requested by Omninuera to evidence, effect, or record such assignment.

8. Code of Conduct and Policies  
- You are expected to follow Omninuera's policies, codes of conduct, data security practices, and reasonable directions from your manager. Non-compliance may result in disciplinary action, up to and including immediate termination for cause.

9. Employment Eligibility and Background Checks  
- This offer is contingent on your ability to provide documentation of your identity and eligibility to perform the internship, and on any background checks or verification procedures required by Omninuera.

10. No Legal Advice; Drafting and Legal Review  
- This document is a draft offer intended for HR and Legal review. It is not legal advice. Omninuera will submit this draft to its Legal team for review and any required revisions.

11. Acceptance  
If you accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy of the signed offer to [HR Contact Email] by signing in the space provided. This offer is not binding until signed by an authorized representative of Omninuera.

Sincerely,

For Omninuera

